Text: Hyaaaaaah!!! Swish, swish, swish, swish, swiiiiish!!!
I got it!!!
When you land a hit, you sure hit big, Gammy!
It seems that your ghostly support is gone.
Dammit! This...this wasn't how it was supposed to go!

I was just gonna spend the rest of my life havin'
fun! What the hell did I ever do to you guys—
It's nothing personal!
Gyaaaaah!!!

But there's plenty of reasons why we'd wanna take you
out. Now, about those Cult archives...where in the
trade city are they?
...B-Below the...hot dog stand...!

Oh, what, there? The place where the bread and meat's
all dry and nasty?

Y-Yeah... Their...dogs really suck...! They could
learn a few things from...Tuna King—
—H-Hey...! I-I know you! You're Novem Silv—
Gehah...!
...It's finished, Lady Alpha.

Nicely done. Can I entrust you with raiding and
collecting information from the archives?

Judging by what the thief said, it seems time is of
the essence. I'll see it done, Lady Alpha.

Now that I know this list of aristocrats is circulating
throughout the Cult, I'll pay attention to trends in
Altena in even more detail.

...So, Gammy, how about this property? With the
little issue of the haunting out of the way,
shouldn't it be okay to buy now?
Well...

If Mitsugoshi were to purchase the manor house now,
it would free the property from its political
entanglements.

It's value would then rise greatly, making it an
ideal subject for the kind of real estate speculation
Eta hopes to see.

The manor house would then become the focal point of
increasingly regular political calculations between
Velgalta and Midgar...

...Say, Lady Alpha! Could this location not perhaps
be used for anything else?
I'm guessing you already have some ideas, Gamma?

Indeed. This place...the Youth Manor House...was once
an affordable lodging facility for Altena's young—

So...I think it would be good if Mitsugoshi were to
do the same thing.

We could open a portion of the residence to intrepid
young globetrotters, while also operating it as a
place of respite for our own Shadow Garden members.

I believe it would better serve us not as a vehicle
for speculation, but as an investment, as the
Mitsugoshi Youth Manor House.

It would both enrich Mitsugoshi's service and
benefits program as well as give us a location to
investigate symptoms of possession among the youth.

Ah yeah, I get it! You're really sharp, Gammy! Guess
it pays to take the long view of things, huh!

...The question of whether every member of the
organization is happy with their lot in life is one
not even Shadow Garden can afford to ignore.

While we don't have thieves like the one we just
dealt with, as our forces grow, it will become
increasingly difficult to keep a grasp of all of our
ranks.

Still, we should find ways to show that the thoughts
of Shadow and the rest of us lie with all of our
members...
...Very well, Gamma.

Though I feel bad for Eta, this property will be
reborn as a youth manor house under the operation of
Mitsugoshi.
Lady Alpha... You have my humble thanks!
Yep, Gammy is gonna Gammy.
What, Iota? Is there something you'd like to say?

No, just noticing that Lady Alpha's got her way of
doing things, and you got yours—
And I got mine! And that's totally cool!

Ciao! Novem Silva here! It's time for Splash Marina's
April evening show!

In this info program, your intrepid Mitsugoshi
influencer will fill you in on all the latest trends
in Grazheim, the city of trade!

You can view this program at six locations around the
city in day and evening showings, with two updates
each month!
Now, let's have a look at the big news for April!

The Youth Manor House owned by Velgalta in
Grazheim...has been sold to Midgar's own Mitsugoshi
for the sum of eight billion zeni!

Mitsugoshi plans to use the location as a recreation
spot for employees, but that's not all...

Parts of the manor and grounds will made available as
accommodations for young travelers and open for
business to sightseers!

No matter who you are or where you're from, you can
get a room for 5,000 zeni per night, breakfast and
beach access included—just as long as you're 25 or
under, that is!
Kids need to travel, and we say let 'em!

Master Shadow, do you remember an operative by the
name of Iota?
Iota... Iota...
Oh yeah. The forest girl.

Yes, the rabbit therianthrope with a taste for forest
bathing and the lush nature of the Kagenou fiefdom.

(Oh, right, her! The fairytale girl with bunny ears
and a sorta organic vibe to her that Alpha found
somewhere.)

I had a face-to-face meeting with Iota for the first
time in quite a while, and from the look of things,
she's become a vapid girl who acts like she's
perpetually on vacation!
Um...so wait...you're saying she's a party girl?
A party girl...?!

Uh, so what I mean is like when a simple kid comes to
the city and gets a real glow up.

Yes, sir! That's exactly it! I simply never expected
her to blend in so completely with her surroundings!

(Hiding behind a bright, bubbly outer persona...
That's one option for playing the part of a side
character.)

(Iota probably avoided copying the exact same traits,
but if even one of our resident actors is shocked...)

(...maybe she underwent a serious transformation,
like totally beyond just playing the part!)

The "party people" look, those "put your hands up"
mannerisms... Perhaps the time will come when I, too,
must master such things...

What?! My lord, you would immerse yourself in such
culture?!

(Nah, let's not start going off on tangents before
I've even mastered the basics of being a side
character... Best forget the party route for now.)

At any rate, there is no denying that Iota has
assimilated fully with her urban environs. Perhaps
there is much to learn from her skills of mimicry!
(Much to learn... Could Lambda become a party girl?)
Hmm...
Master Shadow...?

(...Actually, it might not be such a bad fit. I bet
an actress like her could pull it off no problem.)
Yes... Exercise your abilities to the fullest.
Sir! Yes sir!
